Project Description

This project is designed for personal use within a local WiFi network.
Initially, the project will be deployed on a PC, where it is developed as a server,
but will later be moved to a dedicated server. The project is an application designed
for various interactions between devices within the network: transferring messages, files,
displaying notifications, and so on. The application must be extensible and capable of acquiring
new features. This document is used to document the application's features, both complete and
under development.

The working title of the application is Boobiki.

Tech Stack:
- Server: Python 3.13, FastAPI + Uvicorn
- Client: Web UI served by the server, built as a PWA (Progressive Web App)
- Device discovery: Zeroconf/mDNS (automatic, no manual IP configuration)
- Network: WiFi LAN — no internet required, all communication is local

Design Principles:
- PC and mobile devices must have an equally effective experience
- The Web UI must be fully responsive and installable as a PWA on mobile
- The architecture must be extensible — new features can be added without restructuring
- All devices on the same WiFi network can discover and interact with each other automatically

Features:
- [In Progress] File Transfer: Devices within the local area network should be able to
  exchange files (if device 1 and device 2 are connected to Boobiki, they can transfer
  files directly to each other).